snippet.textDisplay:
Nice video, very polite Cop and very complying suspect.
LIVE PD, please also share the social media links of the COPS who are in the videos so that we can follow them as well and support them like we support LIVE PD .
After watching all these videos, we realise how tough the police job and how risky it is and at the same time realise how we should obey the law and comply with the cops.
Very very good videos to show to our kids and younger brothers from them to learn about the law and why we should respect the police.
During our childhood, our parents could only verbally tell us that we have to obey the police and ask them for help in emergency and not get engaged or even associate with drug related matters.
This new technology and system of educating future generations is very a massive success and we will continue to support LIVE PD and the Law enforcement😊🙏🏽🙏🏽

snippet.textDisplay:
It is the people that have the least that are the nicest most giving, genuine people. They are the ones that will help others out when they need it the most, because they know what it’s feels like too be in need and to be without. How devastating it feels when you have nothing and nobody will help.
It is the people who have a lot that NEVER help, because They have never been in a situation were they were really down and out!
I believe everyone should go through a hard time in their life, it causes them to have real compassion for others.
It helps them too understand what is truly important in life. That the most expensive cars, designer clothes, and top brands are not important, it is the ones you love, your family, the people that you hold dear too you that should mean the most.
Things can be replaced, money is worth nothing if you have no one to share it with!
